---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---
<Base
  title="Monthly Car Rental Dubai — Cheapest Long-Term Deals 2026"
  description="Compare Dubai monthly car rental deals from AED 900/month. Best rates for expats, digital nomads and Virtual Visa holders. No long-term commitment."
>
<div class="bg-teal text-white py-12 px-4 text-center">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-black mb-3">Monthly Car Rental Dubai — From AED 900/Month</h1>
  <p class="text-green-100 mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Best for new expats, digital nomads, and Virtual Visa holders. No ownership. No maintenance. Cancel with 30 days' notice.</p>
  <a href="/get-quotes?ref=monthly" class="bg-yellow-400 text-navy px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-black hover:bg-yellow-300 transition-colors inline-block">Get Monthly Rental Quotes →</a>
</div>

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
  <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow p-4 mb-10">
    <iframe
      src="https://www.discovercars.com/engine/rent-a-car/iframe?a_aid=YOUR_AFFILIATE_ID&location=Dubai&lang=en&curr=AED&period=30"
      width="100%" height="420" frameborder="0" loading="lazy"
      title="Monthly Car Rental Dubai — Compare Prices"
    ></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-brand rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-black text-navy mb-4">Monthly vs Daily — Is Monthly Always Cheaper?</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead><tr class="bg-brand text-white"><th class="p-3 text-left">Car Type</th><th class="p-3">Daily Rate</th><th class="p-3">30 Days (daily)</th><th class="p-3">Monthly Rate</th><th class="p-3">Saving</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          {[
            ["Economy (Yaris/Sunny)","AED 35–55","AED 1,050–1,650","AED 900–1,100","Up to AED 550"],
            ["SUV (RAV4/CR-V)","AED 120–180","AED 3,600–5,400","AED 2,500–3,500","Up to AED 1,900"],
            ["Luxury (BMW/Mercedes)","AED 350–600","AED 10,500–18,000","AED 7,000–12,000","Up to AED 6,000"],
          ].map(r => <tr class="border-b"><td class="p-3 font-medium">{r[0]}</td><td class="p-3 text-center">{r[1]}</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-red-500">{r[2]}</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600 font-bold">{r[3]}</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-teal font-bold">{r[4]}</td></tr>)}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">Rates are approximate. Actual prices depend on operator, insurance level, and mileage allowance.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-navy">Who Should Choose Monthly Car Rental in Dubai?</h2>
    <p>Monthly car rental in Dubai is the fastest-growing segment in the UAE rental market, driven primarily by three groups: newly arrived expats who need mobility before deciding whether to buy a car, digital nomads on the Dubai Virtual Work Residence Visa who stay 1–6 months, and residents whose own car is being serviced or sold.</p>
    <p>The key advantage of monthly rental over daily rental is cost. A 30-day booking on a daily rate for an economy car costs AED 1,050–1,650. The same car on a monthly contract costs AED 900–1,100 — with full insurance, maintenance, and 24/7 roadside assistance included. You save up to AED 550 and gain peace of mind.</p>
    <h3 class="font-bold text-navy">What to Check Before Signing a Monthly Rental Agreement</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Mileage allowance:</strong> Most monthly deals include 3,000–4,000km per month. Excess mileage is charged at AED 0.30–0.50 per kilometre. If you drive a lot, negotiate unlimited mileage upfront.</li>
      <li><strong>Insurance coverage:</strong> Comprehensive insurance (CDW) should be included. Confirm the excess amount — it should be AED 1,500 or lower for an economy car.</li>
      <li><strong>Cancellation terms:</strong> Reputable operators allow cancellation with 30 days' notice. Avoid operators requiring 60+ days' notice.</li>
      <li><strong>Salik (toll) charges:</strong> Salik tags are usually included. Confirm the monthly Salik top-up arrangement before signing.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
</Base>
